==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incorporative
<hw>In*cor"po*ra*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Incorporating or tending to incorporate; <as>as, the
<ex>incorporative</ex> languages (as of the Basques, North American
Indians, etc.</as> ) which run a whole phrase into one word.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>History demonstrates that <qex>incorporative</qex> unions are
solid and permanent; but that a federal union is weak.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Belsham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incorporator</ent>⟦br⟧
